Slide 6 â€“ The 3 Main Rendering Methods
1ï¸âƒ£ SSR â€” Server-Side Rendering
The HTML is generated fresh on every request.
ğŸ“¦ Analogy: Your chef cooks a hot meal ğŸ² every time a customer orders.

Example: News websites (content changes every minute).

2ï¸âƒ£ SSG â€” Static Site Generation
HTML is generated once at build time and reused.
ğŸ“¦ Analogy: Ready-made packaged meal ğŸ± sitting in the fridge, ready to go.

Example: Blogs (content rarely changes).

3ï¸âƒ£ ISR â€” Incremental Static Regeneration
Prebuilt like SSG, but restocked in the background every X seconds.
ğŸ“¦ Analogy: Packaged meals that get restocked every hour so theyâ€™re always fairly fresh.

Example: Product pages where prices change hourly.



